-- Austria's Volksbanken sells Malta unit to MedBank
-- By Michael Shields
-- Fri Apr 11, 2014 05:28AM EDT
-- None



VIENNA, April 11 (Reuters) - Austria's part-nationalised Volksbanken AG <OTVVp.VI> has sold its Volksbank Malta unit to Mediterranean Bank [ANCPFM.UL], it said on Friday, giving no financial details.

After carving out its international business last year, the Maltese business has total assets worth around 150 million euros ($208 million), Volksbanken said in a statement. [ID:nL6N0H11EO]